contentrichtext.text: '''Morgan County''' is the name of eleven counties in the United States of America, nine of which were named for Daniel Morgan, Revolutionary War General: *[[Morgan County, Alabama]] *[[Morgan County, Colorado]] (named for Colonel Christopher A. Morgan) *[[Morgan County, Georgia]] *[[Morgan County, Illinois]] *[[Morgan County, Indiana]] *[[Morgan County, Kentucky]] *[[Morgan County, Missouri]] *[[Morgan County, Ohio]] *[[Morgan County, Tennessee]] *[[Morgan County, Utah]] (named for Jedediah Morgan Grant, father of Heber J. Grant) *[[Morgan County, West Virginia]] {{geodis|uscounty}}
